The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has directed that its party flags at the National Secretariat in Abuja be flown at half-mast in honour of 16 members  who died on Saturday in a motor accident in Plateau. The party’s national publicity secretary, Debo Ologunagba in a statement on Monday, said the PDP family was grief-stricken over the ghastly motor accident. ”Our hearts bleed. Our Party deeply grieves at the loss of these patriotic Nigerians who paid the supreme prize while gallantly devoting their lives in the quest with other compatriots to rescue our nation. READ ALSO: LP Holds-Off Campaign For 3 Days To Honour Plateau Auto Crash Victims “The PDP mourns these courageous patriots who lost their lives in the pursuit of a better country with a purposeful leadership that cares for the wellbeing of all citizens, adding that they shall never be forgotten.” The spokesman said that in honour of the brave compatriots, PDP had directed that its flags at the National Secretariat in Abuja be flown at half-mast while urging Nigerians not to relent in prayers for the nation at this crucial time. Ologunagba commiserated with the victims families, prayed God grants them grace to bear the loss and to heal the injured with speedy recovery. 